   <note type="biography">
      <p>Birth: Otley, Yorkshire, England (16 February 1840)</p>
      <p>Death: London (04 April 1917)</p>
      
      <p>Career: Took over his father's business; entered Leeds Borough Council (1869); MP for Leeds (1880-1885); MP for North Division of Leeds (1885-1902); Financial Secretary to the Treasury (1885-1886 and 1886-1891); Privy Councillor (1890); Chief Secretary for Ireland (1891-1892); Lord Mayor (1895); Chairman, Great Northern Railway (18995-1908)</p>
      <p>Honours: Baron 1902</p>
      
      <p>Membership: Fellow</p>
      <p>Election Date: 5/02/1891</p>
   </note>
